    <div class="article comment" id="cid-1487104">
      <p class="text">It looks just delicious - and what a beautiful presentation.  I am not fond of graham crackers (or vanilla wafers) so I will probably try some kind of tea biscuit instead.  <br>About some of the comments - kudos to those on diets who can make a low-cal substitute!   If you don't like Fat Free Cool Whip don't use it.  But if you need  a lo-cal substitute for whipped cream it tastes OK and let's face it, obesity is a MUCH larger health risk than ingesting a bit of Cool Whip!  And by the way the jury is still out on the dangers of high-fructose corn syrup; there is no definitive evidence thus far that it is less healthful then regular table sugar.</p>
