    <div class="article comment" id="cid-1547031">
      <p class="text">I made this exactly as per recipe for a dinner party last night and it was definitely a success. However, I found that I did not need nearly as much whipped cream in the end. I spread it relatively thin (like triple what I'd do with jam or peanut butter on a sandwich) and I had at least a cup of whipped cream left over, so you might could go a little lower. Also, I found the whipped cream a little too sweet for grown-ups and next time I will add even less sugar. My berries were tightly packed, but next time I will crowd them in even tighter in each layer to have that strawberry flavour shine even more. Thanks for a great idea. Everyone at our party thought the dessert was a show-stopper.</p>
      <div class="footer meta">
            posted by
            <a href="http://community.apartmenttherapy.com/users/346658">aimeebama</a>
